column5: Any construction on "17" North of the Soo? Also Route 631 North of White River. Assistance appreciated. Traveling there June 1.
Take a look at the following web reference for the information you want:http://www.roadinfo.mto.gov.on.ca/en...ion/index.html
Construction info and maps not available from above site.
Worked for me. Shows road construction in Ontario.
Worked for me too this morning! Just have to keep clicking to get to the details.

I was back and forth between Wawa and Sault this weekend , and there was NO construction...not even any hint of construction with survey stakes....So clear sailing to Wawa. BUT .....lots of moose . We saw five randomly along route and near the road in broad daylight ....so keep your eyes open, watch for flashing headlights of drivers giving you warning too. Night time driving would be even more dangerous ! Those moose have a tendency to deconstruct a car or truck jake

If I was returning to Wawa and parts North this year(unfortunately I'm not) I would not even be disappointed if there was construction. The ride from the Soo to Wawa has got to be the most beautiful scenery I have ever laid eyes on. The Eastern shore of Lake Superior is something to see. I can't even imagine what it looks like when the leaves turn. So enjoy it, construction or not!!!
